Question: How would you invite your friends to a party if phones and the Internet did not exist?
Answer:
If phones and the internet did not exist, I would invite friends to a party using letters or verbally. Letters are nice because they feel sentimental, and because if you write a letter the person will kniw that you really want them to come. Verbally is easiest if you will see them anyway, because you can tell them details and don't have to write things down.